  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of<strong> cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-steak-with-chunky-pineapple-salsa/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">While the rice is cooking, combine</span> the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>allspice</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) on a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>jerk seasoning</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-steak-with-chunky-pineapple-salsa/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the fat from the <strong>pork loin steaks</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>pork loin steaks</strong> to the <strong>jerk seasoning</strong> and turn them until they're fully coated in all the spices</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-steak-with-chunky-pineapple-salsa/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated pork loin steaks</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until they're browned and cooked through</p>\n<p>Transfer the <strong>cooked steaks</strong> to a clean chopping board, cover with a clean tea towel and leave them to rest for 2 min<span class=\"text-highlight\"> – these are your <strong>spicy pork steaks</strong></span></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-steak-with-chunky-pineapple-salsa/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice the <strong>spring onions</strong> finely</p>\n<p>Drain and roughly chop the<strong> pineapple slices</strong></p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> into quarters </p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-steak-with-chunky-pineapple-salsa/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped pineapple</strong> and <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> with most of the <strong>spring onion</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> (save the rest for garnish!)</p>\n<p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the<strong> juice</strong> of 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span> <strong>lime</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>pineapple salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-steak-with-chunky-pineapple-salsa/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Finely slice the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>rested spicy pork steaks</strong></span></p>\n<p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-steak-with-chunky-pineapple-salsa/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>sliced spicy pork steaks</strong> </span>with the<strong> brown rice</strong> and<strong> pineapple salsa</strong> to the side</p>\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>remaining juice</strong> from the <strong>pineapple salsa </strong>all over</p>\n<p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining spring onion</strong>,<strong> coriander</strong> and<strong> lime wedge</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
